description.narrative: UNICEF has provided concerted support to the MoH to ensure continuity of essential Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn, Child and Adolescent Health (RMNCAH) services through the report period marred by the worsening Covid19 pandemic situation. However, service disruptions (for many reasons) has resulted in a lower coverage for key interventions compared to 2019. About 6,238 pregnant women received first ANC services between March and May as against 8,835 women during the same period in 2019, while 65% of children received MCV1 (April to June) as against 91% in the corresponding period of 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
